EFLTK - Extended Fast Light Toolkit Version 2.0.4

-------------------------------------------------

WHAT IS EFLTK?
	EFltk is a LGPL'd C++ graphical user interface toolkit for 
	X (UNIX(r)), OpenGL(r), and Microsoft(r) Windows(r). 
	It is based on FLTK2 (see README.fltk) and is currently
	developed by Equinox Desktop Environment Team (ede.sf.net)

CHANGES BETWEEN FLTK2 AND EFLTK
	See 'ChangeLog' file for description of changes.

DOCUMENTATION
	Sorry, no API documentation yet.
  Please see header files and/or FLTK2 documentation
  at http://www.fltk.org/documentation.html

BUILDING AND INSTALLING EFLTK

	EFltk is developed and tested with following machines:
	- MS Windows 98, 2000, XP
	- Redhat Linux 7.3/GCC 3.2
	- Solaris 8/GCC 3.2 (Sparc)	

	Unix style machines:
		type: ./build.gcc --'options'
		Where 'options' can be e.g. --enable-gl
		type: su -c "make install"

	Windows:
		MSVC++ is supported 'efltk/visualc'
		MINGW 2.0 is also supported 'elfkt/MinGW'

INTERNET RESOURCES

	EFLTK is available on the 'net in a bunch of locations:

	- WWW:   http://ede.sourceforge.net

	- CVS:	 http://www.sourceforge.net/projects/ede

	- EMail: Laza@Flashmail.com

REPORTING BUGS

	To report a bug in EFLTK, send an email to "Laza@Flashmail.com",
        or use our bug tracking system at sourceforge.
	Please include the EFLTK version, operating system & version, and
	compiler that you are using when describing the bug or problem.

	For general support and questions, please use the EFLTK mailing
	list at "ede-users@lists.sourceforge.net".

